casebody.data:
Thursday, April 9, 1992

MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

91-825. Charlie’s Dodge, Inc. v. Celebrezze.

Lucas County, No. L-90-086. This cause, here on appeal from the Court of Appeals for Lucas County, was considered in the manner prescribed by law. Upon consideration of appellants’ application to dismiss,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that said application be, and the same is hereby, granted, effective April 7, 1992.

ACCORDINGLY, IT IS FURTHER ORDERED by the court that this cause be, and hereby is, dismissed.
